content:
The error message you are getting suggests that there is a problem with the URL you are using to push your local Git repository to GitHub.

It looks like the URL you provided has an extra "https" in it. Try running the following command instead:
```csharp
git remote add origin https://github.com/username-parveen/webgem.git
```
This should add the remote repository URL to your local Git repository without any issues. Make sure to replace "username-parveen" with your actual GitHub username.

After adding the remote repository, you should be able to push your local repository to GitHub using the following command:
```perl
git push -u origin master
```
This should push your changes to the remote repository on GitHub.
